    "_id": "jn780pzjkgn2dq9geb9mqq7b4h83vcb9",
    "createdBy": "kd795pd2q713d3q8q22z5d4a7s822ec0",
    "description": "The threat model must distinguish between run mode (three safety layers: process groups + revoke-on-exit + TTL) and mint mode (one layer: TTL). Must acknowledge /proc/*/environ risks, credential logging via env vars, fork inheritance to grandchildren, and the SIGKILL gap honestly. Must not claim simplicity equals security.",
    "projectId": "9887a770-ff7d-44d4-aeeb-a9c7b2252b73",
